    "type": "message",
    "text": "what comes to my mind:\nwhen the programmers works on a piece of code, they are working with 3 views or layers: syntax, semantics, domain-specific knowledge.\n\nAt the syntax level are the keywords, the spaces or brackets, the specific symbols that they have to chain in the right way for the parser to make sense of.\n\nAt the semantic level they are working with the nodes of the AST. They are creating, modifying or destroying a conditional, a pattern matching expression, reference to a variable, a literal, etc.\n\nAt the domain-specific level, they are working with the rules that govern a system. You authenticate something, like a `User`, you commit or rollback  `Transaction` . these are your types or classes and the operations they support",
